RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 10800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DATS A SUPERSTAR secured the lead past the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, contested a slim advantage nearest the rail on the turn, dueled clear leaving the eighth pole and was steadily handled to hold on well. SK'S HEART gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn about the four path, closed steadily through the lane and took second in the final strides. LATE NIGHT SPIRIT pressured the pace through the backstretch and contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn, but dropped back past the eighth pole and flattened stride the final sixteenth. FIDDLERSHOTPLEASUR gave chase, raced in the five path on the turn and passed rivals outside. EVERYDAYISAGIFT pressured the pace inside but dropped back nearing the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn and flattened in the lane. PRINCESS MIA ROSE chased, rounded the turn about the three path and weakened. TODAYISMYDAY chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, angled out past the eighth pole and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace inside,dropped back near 1/4,rail turn,flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Dats a Superstar
ENTRY.COMMENT: up 2d past 7/16,set pressured pace,rail turn,held well driving

ENTRY.NAME: Sk's Heart
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,4p turn,steadily closed lane,up 2nd final strides

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,angled out past 1/8,little in lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 12700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 12, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 12 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4, 000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: READY AND RICH rounded the opening turn about the four path then stalked into the backstretch, closed to a challenging position approaching the three eighths pole and took the nod two deep toward the quarter, raced clear into the stretch and was kept alert to eventually widen. RRACE DAY WARRIOR was bumped leaving the gate then took over approaching the thirteen sixteenths pole and rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, was met toward the quarter, raced at the rail on the far turn then flattened the final sixteenth. INDIANA RED rated close inside, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly down the lane. CURLIN'S THRILL settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the five path and showed little further. MONGOLIAN HERO bobbled outward and made contact with Rrace Day Warrior leaving the gate, rounded the first turn in the three path and picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn but showed little in the lane. MAKE WAY settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole then faded in the three path on the far turn. JUST NOD AND SMILE stalked off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded leaving the three eighths.

ENTRY.NAME: Mongolian Hero
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled break,3p 1st turn,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANDY FOR JUBA took a quick lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under some pressure approaching the five sixteenths pole, widened at the rail on the far turn and extended his lead under mostly a vigorous hand ride. CHRISTOPHER'SHEART ducked out and made contact with Bradley Do Right leaving the gate then stalked from the three path, gave chase past the half mile pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and had to settle for second best. YACHTSMEN was bumped leaving the gate then settled well back inside on the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, steadily improved three wide on the far turn but showed little more. AYE CALYPSO stalked off the rail the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. GREATEST NOTION saved ground off the pace then faded through the backstretch. BRADLEY DO RIGHT was bumped outward and into Yachtsmen leaving the gate, raced in the four path the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. GOOD BUZZ raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: Candy for Juba
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 5/16,widened turn,hand urged lane

ENTRY.NAME: Yachtsmen
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,settled inside,chased 3/8,3wd far turn,little left

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 15700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility)(Races Whe re Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR CHANCE ROMANCE took over while moving to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and held on under steady handling. PRESSURE rounded the first turn in the four path, challenged toward the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path on the far turn and finished well while gaining on the winner. RAGTIME RICHES saved ground off the pace, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, then dueled through the stretch for third. LEG UP saved ground off the pace, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. NIGHT TRAIN WAYNE stalked two deep then gave chase toward the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. DIVINAS CONNECTION raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the nine sixteenths pole and eased outward into the backstretch, gave chase from the half mile pole, rounded the far turn about the five path and showed little more.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured near 3/8,rail turn,held on driving

ENTRY.NAME: Pressure
ENTRY.OWNER: Baccari Racing Stable LLC and Prince Chester

ENTRY.NAME: Divinas Connection

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LONA LEE took the lead at the half mile pole and set a pressured pace, dueled clear toward the quarter, raced at the rail on the turn and was steadily handled to hold well. MISS BEE BOP gave close chase through the backstretch, dropped back approaching the quarter pole, raced evenly in the lane but had to settle for second best. FRIEND FURH REAL became fractious behind the gate then gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. SHOTGUN MARGARET gave chase, raced at the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. BEVERLY'SACTINUP chased outside, raced in the five path on the turn and finished evenly. WAY OF APPEAL chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path and flattened in the lane. IMADHI veered in at the break then gave chase, though, weakened in the four path on the turn. SING ME TO SLEEP ducked in break and raced well back. SPIRIT ON THE WIND was shut off at the break and saved ground. My Lucky Deia ran loose in the post parade and was a late scratch.

ENTRY.NAME: Friend Furh Real
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious at gate,chased inside,rail turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Lona Lee
ENTRY.COMMENT: up 1/2,set pressured pace,clear near 1/4,held well driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 78. Allowance Purse 28400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 12 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 12 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered F or $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'M THE MONEY MAN settled in the three path on the opening turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail then dug in under steady encouragement to take the nod under the wire. I'LLTAKECAREOFIT rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole and contested the advantage at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady handling leaving the turn and bested NOCASHREFUNDS for second but was nipped for the win under the wire. The latter stalked off the rail, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. DON'TCALLTOOEARLY raced in the four path the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, had his heels clipped in the four path and ran evenly in the stretch. NEVERPOPTHECORK saved ground off the pace, picked up the chase approaching the seven sixteenths pole then eased out from the heels of ROAD SLEW past the quarter pole and had his heels clipped, but ran evenly in the lane. The latter stalked from the three path the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, moved to the rail at the quarter pole and flattened in the lane. MY BOY CLYDE settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but was forced out and clipped the heels of Don'tcalltooearly past the quarter pole, fell, but got up and walked off. After posting the inquiry, the Stewards disqualified Neverpopthecork to sixth place for causing the incident past the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: I'm the Money Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3p 1st turn,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,off rail turn,nod at wire

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 24000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-w inners Of A Race Since September 12 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 12 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KENNY HAD A NOTION stalked from the three path the first turn, dueled to the lead approaching the five sixteenths pole, raced clear nearing the quarter and held on under steady stretch handling. ALLEN CAN DO IT settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, dueled clear in second past the eighth pole and finished evenly while gaining on the waning winner. MARTINKELLY settled off the rail, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path then dueled through the stretch for third. STARBURST rated a slim lead off the rail past the five eighths pole, came under pressure past the three eighths and was met toward the five sixteenths, dropped back into the far turn and flattened in the lane. NEWS BOX rounded the first turn in the five path, gave chase from the five sixteenths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little in the lane. BOURBON THUNDER raced off the rail on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. CLASSY AMERICAN became fractious in the gate which necessitated a late rider change, rated just off the early pace in the four path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the five path on the far turn. MIND YOUR OWN raced with the early pace inside but dropped back toward the half mile pole, gave chase approaching the seven sixteenths but weakened toward the quarter pole. CURLIN'S MALIBU raced well back.

ENTRY.NAME: Martinkelly
ENTRY.OWNER: Two Ten Twelve Triple T Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Starburst
ENTRY.OWNER: Dare To Dream Stable LLC (Michael Faber)

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligib ility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKED WISDOM tapered in and stalked from the three path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole and took the nod passing the five sixteenths pole, was met at even terms nearest the rail midway on the far turn but dug in under determined handling to hold on. KATALIMA settled close off the rail the first turn, started a four wide bid approaching the three eighths pole and dueled to even terms three wide midway on the far turn, cleared second in later yards but couldn't improve on the winner. MISS LAUREN stalked off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from the five sixteenths, raced between horses two deep on the far turn but started to flatten stride nearing mid-stretch. TENNIS TAP saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and raced off the rail on the far turn, eased outward leaving the turn and showed little further. TAPPING SOUTH raced well off the pace in the four path the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and passed some rivals. BOCA BIRDIE was not a factor. MOIRAINE took over and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure into the backstretch, was met at the five sixteenths pole and faded readily at the rail on the far turn. WISHING FOR SPRING had a brief early lead then rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Tennis Tap
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.COMMENT: brief early lead,rated close,chased 7/16,faded far turn
